abstract: Initial statements from Iran and Ukraine were contradictory, and the cause of the crash remains unclear. The planeâ€™s so-called black boxes could help, but Iranian officials may not turn them over to Boeing.
lead_paragraph: On Wednesday morning, a passenger plane bound for Ukraine exploded as it slammed into a field in Iran, just minutes after takeoff. The Boeing jet was operated by a Ukrainian carrier, and at least 176 people were on board. None survived.
